		"description": "{html}<div><p>Loading stereo sound using the following code:<br></p>\n<pre>\n<code class=\"javascript\">var waitingSound = Ti.Media.createSound({\n  url: 'sounds/twing.caf'\n});</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Then sleeping OS X will max out the CPU until the simulator is\nclosed or the app is backgrounded. Using the exact same code to\nload a mono audio file will not cause this problem. I've attached\nthe original stereo file (twing.mp3), and a mono version\n(twing.caf).</p>\n<p>The same thing happens when saved as a stereo *.caf file, so I'm\npretty sure it's not because of the file format.</p></div>{html}",
